1
00:00:09,886 --> 00:00:10,695
(The Thai people want...)

2
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:12,519
We need justice.

3
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:16,159
Bring our people back.

4
00:00:16,160 --> 00:00:19,439
We need justice.

5
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:23,000
Bring our people back.

6
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:25,559
Hey! I said get out.

7
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:27,880
Hurry up.. Get out of the building.

8
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:30,280
Hey!

9
00:00:33,160 --> 00:00:34,759
Hey! You guys.

10
00:00:34,760 --> 00:00:36,120
Get out of the building!

11
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:39,479
Quick!

12
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:41,159
Go, go!

13
00:00:41,160 --> 00:00:42,440
Hurry up.

14
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:45,160
Get out!

15
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:47,759
There is no one left here.

16
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:48,879
Hurry up! Quick!

17
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:50,280
Go go go!

18
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:53,399
How are things now, Ravin?
Have you cleared everyone out?

19
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,400
Done. Go!

20
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Hurry up!

21
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,560
I think there's no one here.

22
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:03,959
You two, go check at the back building.

23
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:04,640
Where'll you go?

24
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:05,640
I'll check the leaders.

25
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:06,919
Wait, Ravin.

26
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:07,920
Be careful.

27
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:09,480
Come, Mada.

28
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Go around that way.

29
00:01:15,001 --> 00:01:16,320
What about the Law building?

30
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:17,576
There's no one left at the Law building.

31
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:18,999
I'll check at the Social Sciences building.

32
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,336
I'll check at the Accountancy building.

33
00:01:20,360 --> 00:01:20,880
OK.

34
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:21,880
Be careful.

35
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,560
Mai!

36
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,400
Stop.

37
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:44,080
Hello.

38
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:51,040
What?

39
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:04,920
Remember to go to the meeting point
when you get out.

40
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:18,560
Our friends out there
are preparing to go to the forest.

41
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:21,279
If we want to reform the country,

42
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:23,760
we must go where there's opportunity.

43
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,640
Do you want to join us?

44
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:39,800
If so, what do I have to do?

45
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,360
I'll tell you where to meet later.

46
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:58,480
Lieutenant Det, could you allow me to see my son?

47
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:02,520
Please, Lieutenant.

48
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:04,640
Sure, teacher.

49
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:05,640
Thanks so much.

50
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:08,760
Vin.

51
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:10,760
Mom.

52
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:12,600
Vin, are you ok?

53
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:17,880
Did you get hurt?

54
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:23,120
I'll try to bail you out.

55
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:26,640
All of you, too.

56
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,560
Please calm down.

57
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,200
I'm here for the arrested students.

58
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,000
This way.

59
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:27,800
"When Light Fades"
(Episode 1)

60
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,520
Dan told me he'll come tomorrow.

61
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,280
Don't forget to thank him properly.

62
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,400
If it wasn't for him,

63
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:09,800
I wouldn't know how to get you out.

64
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,120
OK, mom.

65
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,800
He moved away a long time ago.

66
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:23,400
Never thought I'd see him helping us.

67
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,680
Guess we're lucky.

68
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:33,960
...have fled into the jungle to
join the Communist Party of Thailand.

69
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:39,359
Such actions are considered
a grave threat to national security.

70
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:42,320
I don't want you to join this.

71
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,439
Your duty is to study.

72
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:49,040
Leave the national affairs to the others.

73
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,480
Mom.

74
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:57,480
I just want to make this country better.

75
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:02,120
I went to the volunteer
camp in the countryside.

76
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,720
There's a lot of exploitation out there.

77
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:07,400
Inequality is everywhere.

78
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:11,440
I know you want to make our country better,

79
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:17,199
but there are many methods to do that.

80
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:19,560
Please don't follow the trend.

81
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:22,160
There's no need to go
to protests like this.

82
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,560
Do you understand me?

83
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:31,360
Yes I do.

84
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:23,640
My friends and I...

85
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,560
We might just be small, ordinary people.

86
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,480
But our hearts are 'great'

87
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:35,080
enough to believe that equality must exist.

88
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,680
No matter how much we must endure.

89
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,280
Because the people we love most...

90
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:42,920
Deserve to live in a better world.

91
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:48,960
My name is Ravin. It means 'The Sun'.

92
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,760
The sun's duty isn't just to shine,

93
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:55,360
it's to give light to everyone, equally.

94
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,680
And true light...

95
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:01,000
doesn't shine for itself;

96
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:03,640
it shines so that others can see the way.

97
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:07,680
Even the smallest person
can be a 'Great Sun'

98
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:09,680
for someone else.

99
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,440
Get off, kids.

100
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,080
Ouch!

101
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,240
Are we here?

102
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,040
Just answer this if you meet anyone.

103
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:44,920
"Though the sky is dark, the stars remain."

104
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,719
Yes sir.

105
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:49,800
Keep it quiet.

106
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,080
What's next?

107
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,480
Who?

108
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:15,520
Who?

109
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:17,920
We...

110
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:20,560
Though the sky is dark, the stars remain.

111
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,280
Is that all of you?

112
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:46,800
Good, let's go.

113
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,480
Uh... wait a moment.

114
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:51,880
I...

115
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,719
I have a stomachache.

116
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,960
Poo?

117
00:10:56,520 --> 00:10:57,720
Stomachache.

118
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:58,680
Just wait a moment.

119
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:01,400
If you want to poo, go there.

120
00:11:02,873 --> 00:11:04,160
The rest will wait here.

121
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,359
Any tissue paper?

122
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:09,960
Nope! Who uses tissue paper in the forest?

123
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:13,600
Beware of soldiers.

124
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,120
Beware of soldiers.

125
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:24,880
Phew! Almost didn't make it.

126
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:33,320
Do I really need leaves to wipe my ass?

127
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:38,880
Whatever.

128
00:11:40,680 --> 00:11:43,360
Ouch!

129
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:08,400
Which way?

130
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:25,080
Ouch!

131
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:32,080
Ouch!!

132
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,080
Get up!

133
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:58,640
Get up!

134
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,240
Sorry.

135
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,040
Thank you so much for saving me.

136
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:09,240
Be careful if you don't
want to die in the forest.

137
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:12,280
Thank you so much for saving me.

138
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:14,400
My name is Ravin.

139
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:18,360
You can call me Vin.

140
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,400
What do you want me to call you?

141
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:31,920
Comrade Yue.

142
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:38,079
Yeh... Yoh... Yeh... Yeow...

143
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:38,960
Yue.

144
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:39,800
Yea.

145
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,800
Yue.

146
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:42,280
Yeah...

147
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:43,040
Yeww.

148
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:43,920
Yue.

149
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:44,760
Yea.

150
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:45,760
Comrade Yue.

151
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:47,800
Yeww.

152
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:53,720
Yak.

153
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:56,680
Stop.

154
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:59,520
Keep quiet, just follow me.

155
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:06,440
Yes, Comrade Yak.

156
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:10,200
What kind of person lacks social skills?

157
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:21,520
I think he's been gone too long.

158
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:23,280
I'm gonna go find him.

159
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:26,760
Please take care of the students.

160
00:14:27,160 --> 00:14:28,160
Yes sir.

161
00:14:30,857 --> 00:14:33,696
Hey! Why did you take this path, comrade?

162
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,840
What about the path you explored?

163
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:41,800
Why did you two come together?

164
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:47,240
Everyone is here. Let's go.

165
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,160
What took you so long?

166
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,360
I got a little lost.

167
00:14:58,160 --> 00:14:59,480
I tripped.

168
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:02,960
Luckily, Yak saved me.

169
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:05,960
Yak? Is that his name?

170
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:07,960
Yep.

171
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:11,920
What the hell... Yak?

172
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:16,440
What a weird name. Yak? Seriously?

173
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:18,600
Yes it is.

174
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,840
My legs are dragging.
When will I get there?

175
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,440
Totally.

176
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:03,760
Ouch!

177
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:08,080
Let me carry your bag.

178
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:19,160
Have some water first.
It'll help you feel better.

179
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,000
Can I have some? I'm all out.

180
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:31,040
Umm.

181
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:50,600
Yak.

182
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,440
Yak.

183
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,040
Yak, Yak.

184
00:16:55,960 --> 00:16:56,960
How far?

185
00:16:58,480 --> 00:17:01,640
A bit more... just go
over that mountain.

186
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,880
The mountain? A bit more?

187
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:08,880
Yak.

188
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,720
How far do we have to go to reach the base?

189
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:16,960
I think you're tired because
you're talking too much.

190
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:19,480
Just shut up and keep walking.

191
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:23,800
We're all tired. Can
we have a little break?

192
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:34,320
If you can't take this,

193
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:37,200
you should go back
to university, right?

194
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:47,640
Give it to her.

195
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:54,640
There's a stream up ahead, don't stop yet.

196
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,560
Fine, just a bit more.

197
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:02,880
Hey!

198
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:05,759
Drink first. Hang in there.

199
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:06,760
He said...

200
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:09,200
A-BIT-MORE.

201
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:11,800
Go.

202
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:31,240
Everyone.

203
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:33,560
Tonight we will take a rest here.

204
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:36,440
Phew!

205
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:12,600
Everyone is ready to eat.

206
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:19,120
Go ahead. I just wanna
rest here for a while.

207
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,440
If you want to stay together in the base,
stick to the rules.

208
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,200
When it's time to eat, you eat.

209
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,400
When it's time to work, you work.

210
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,600
Don't just do whatever you feel like.

211
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:36,360
Yes sir, Comrade Yak.

212
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,720
Why do you have to be so forceful?

213
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:10,680
Why can't you see the big anthill?

214
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,880
If it's a mine, you'd be done for.

215
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:41,040
This is for you.

216
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:43,800
Thank you.

217
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:45,320
Mr.?

218
00:20:46,473 --> 00:20:49,353
Just call me Yaguar. I'm
only a villager who volunteered.

219
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:51,719
Thank you.

220
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:53,040
Sure.

221
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:00,040
Hey!

222
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:04,480
Come here, come come.

223
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:05,960
Come here. Sit together.

224
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,000
Hurry up, comrade.

225
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,960
Sit here.

226
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,160
Eat it.

227
00:21:24,160 --> 00:21:26,680
It's OK. I can sit with my friends.

228
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,320
So you can eat your fill.

229
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:31,560
You can share with me.

230
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:34,120
Why share?

231
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:35,919
We got equally tired walking,

232
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:37,280
so we should eat equally.

233
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:40,560
Then we'll have enough strength to walk.

234
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:42,040
Eat it.

235
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:53,040
What is this meat? It tastes gamey.

236
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:57,120
It's dog meat.

237
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,360
We're in a forest, not in a city.

238
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:07,240
We eat to live,

239
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:09,240
not live to eat.

240
00:22:15,720 --> 00:22:16,720
Eat it.

241
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:23,040
Sila.

242
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:28,720
As they said, we have to adjust to living.

243
00:22:29,153 --> 00:22:30,273
If we can't bear this,

244
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:32,240
how will we handle tougher things?

245
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,800
It might be rough at first.

246
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:39,759
You should try to eat. It's cold at night.

247
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:41,240
Dog meat can keep you warm.

248
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:08,800
Mada.

249
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:16,519
It's not easy to find food in the forest.
If it's edible, eat it.

250
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:19,760
Please don't be a burden to others.

251
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:25,400
Isn't that too harsh?

252
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:28,800
It's alright, Mada.

253
00:23:30,360 --> 00:23:31,480
Go take a seat.

254
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:47,800
Try harder, so you'll have the strength.

255
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:56,399
Come here, sit with us.

256
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:57,759
I want to sit with my friends.

257
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:58,640
Nope.

258
00:23:58,640 --> 00:23:59,600
Let me sit with Mada.

259
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:00,480
Nope.

260
00:24:00,481 --> 00:24:02,440
Sit down.

261
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:05,040
Eat it.

262
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:07,600
Try harder, so you'll have the strength.

263
00:24:11,880 --> 00:24:16,120
Yummy! I've never ever tasted it before.

264
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:18,680
So delicious, very delicious.

265
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:23,120
Good. So finish it.
Tomorrow you have to walk a lot.

266
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,000
Fine! I will.

267
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:45,920
Vin has been gone a couple of days.

268
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:51,120
I asked Mada's mom. She told me...

269
00:24:52,520 --> 00:24:54,560
Mada has been gone with Sila as well.

270
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:00,360
I'm afraid, Dan.

271
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:06,720
I'm afraid that Vin would
have gone to the forest.

272
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:16,960
Don't worry, Aunt La-or.

273
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:19,680
I'll find out about Vin.

274
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:22,520
And will call you as soon
as I get the information.

275
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:30,360
Let me get the phone.

276
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:31,400
Sure.

277
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:04,560
Vin.

278
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:07,560
Are you hurt?

279
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:10,399
Don't worry. You will be fine.

280
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,920
Go rest up there.

281
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:21,120
Eat this, Dan.

282
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:24,120
It's good. You should try some.

283
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:26,480
Eat more, so you can grow faster.

284
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:42,360
I'll bring you home, Vin.

285
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:27,840
New Student List: Baan Saeng Dao Base.

286
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:32,881
Comrade Ploeng,
do you know Ravin ShineShan's background?

287
00:27:34,080 --> 00:27:35,640
Have you been thinking about it?

288
00:27:37,120 --> 00:27:39,399
Having the same last
name or being siblings,

289
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:41,520
doesn't mean they know each other.

290
00:27:42,360 --> 00:27:45,320
Whatever happens out
there, stays out there.

291
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:48,120
Our ideology here is more important.

292
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:04,680
Ravin and his two friends
who are student leaders, are interesting.

293
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:07,880
They have passion and determination,

294
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:10,120
and can really help us with this mission.

295
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:26,639
We need justice.

296
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:30,239
Bring our people back.

297
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:33,439
We need justice.

298
00:28:33,440 --> 00:28:37,079
Bring our people back.

299
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:38,360
We have no weapons.

300
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:40,199
Don't shoot us.

301
00:28:40,200 --> 00:28:41,680
Don't shoot our people.

302
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:47,000
Help me, Vin.

303
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:22,240
Crying?

304
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:39,440
I had a bad dream.

305
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:44,520
I dreamnt about the university that day.

306
00:29:52,320 --> 00:29:53,840
Forget about everything
outside of the forest.

307
00:29:57,840 --> 00:29:59,760
You've chosen to be here in the forest.

308
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:03,120
So please stick to the ideology.

309
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:05,840
Follow our revolutionary path.

310
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:15,320
I know it's not that easy.

311
00:30:17,840 --> 00:30:19,360
But that doesn't mean it's impossible.

312
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:23,040
I've been through it before.

313
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:31,360
How did you get through it?

314
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:38,600
You'll see.

315
00:30:43,840 --> 00:30:46,240
Get some sleep, we've got
a long way to go tomorrow.

316
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:54,480
Thanks for taking care of me.

317
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,000
Are you OK, Mada?

318
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:05,599
How far does it take to reach the base?

319
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:06,680
Almost there.

320
00:32:12,233 --> 00:32:13,553
Mr. Yak said almost there.

321
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:16,240
But I think it means
there's still a mountain.

322
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:19,920
Just keep walking. I'm too tired to talk.

323
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:25,040
That kid is really mischievous.

324
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:38,080
This is it. The entrance of our base.

325
00:33:16,760 --> 00:33:22,040
(The villages surround the
city, the people must prevail.)

326
00:33:25,826 --> 00:33:28,066
The newbie young comrades have arrived!

327
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:49,520
Welcome to Baan Saeng Dao's base, comrades.

328
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:57,600
One of the allies of
Communist Party of Thailand.

329
00:33:58,360 --> 00:34:00,040
Welcome.

330
00:34:01,760 --> 00:34:05,399
Yes! We're here.

331
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:06,880
Finally we made it!

332
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:07,840
(Comrades, victory belongs to the people._

333
00:35:08,593 --> 00:35:10,993
Hello again, every new comrade.

334
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:15,120
From now on we are one family.

335
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:18,480
We stay together as comrades.

336
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:23,920
We'll share joy, pain,
and the same ideology.

337
00:35:24,377 --> 00:35:26,696
Whatever happens outside, stays outside.

338
00:35:26,720 --> 00:35:31,040
Here, we won't ask about
your past or background.

339
00:35:31,640 --> 00:35:33,160
For security,

340
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:36,880
we use aliases
instead of our real names.

341
00:35:38,680 --> 00:35:41,600
If anyone already has one in mind, tell us.

342
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:45,600
I will go by Comrade Gaun Hin.

343
00:35:45,640 --> 00:35:48,840
I want to be like a rock.
Stay strong and unshakable for our country.

344
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:51,960
Mhm, good!

345
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:56,760
I will go by Comrade Meut.

346
00:35:57,680 --> 00:35:59,240
I will go by Comrade Dum.

347
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:03,960
Mhm, Comrade Meut, Comrade Dum. Great!

348
00:36:05,520 --> 00:36:06,520
Who's Ravin?

349
00:36:08,679 --> 00:36:09,879
When did you create your alias?

350
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:12,360
The one who's talking to Comrade Gaun Hin.

351
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:16,640
People need to be prepared.

352
00:36:20,040 --> 00:36:21,720
Do you think he is involved with that guy?

353
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:24,520
Don't know yet.

354
00:36:27,080 --> 00:36:28,280
What about you two?

355
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:32,120
We haven't thought anything yet.

356
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:36,360
Well, you go by Comrade Ying.

357
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:41,800
Good. Thank you, Comrade Ploeng.

358
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:43,320
What about you?

359
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:46,440
He is Comrade Saeng.

360
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:56,520
All right, Comrade
Saeng. Then it's settled.

361
00:36:56,720 --> 00:36:58,799
All of the new comrades

362
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:01,160
please get your personal belongings
at the quartermaster.

363
00:37:01,400 --> 00:37:06,560
We will treat each other with honor,
and respect here.

364
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:10,280
Shit! I don't like the name
'Comrade Saeng', so lame.

365
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:16,960
We do not use swear words here.
Not even "shit" or "damn."

366
00:37:19,160 --> 00:37:20,200
Shit! Me again.

367
00:37:22,066 --> 00:37:23,626
He's just said not to use "shit."

368
00:37:25,040 --> 00:37:28,040
If we're all clear, dismissed.

369
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:41,560
Hey Comrade! Take it.

370
00:37:44,160 --> 00:37:46,439
Hand everything out.

371
00:37:46,440 --> 00:37:48,720
I don't like the name "Comrade Saeng."

372
00:37:50,720 --> 00:37:52,040
Comrade.

373
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:57,960
Wait a minute. I'll be back.

374
00:37:59,440 --> 00:38:03,120
Yak. Yak. Yak.

375
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:07,120
Yak. Yak.

376
00:38:10,600 --> 00:38:13,199
We already have a title.
You can call me a comrade.

377
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:15,680
Sure, Comrade Yak.

378
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:17,560
Please pronounce it correctly.

379
00:38:19,560 --> 00:38:27,480
Comrade Yue... Comrade Yue! Comrade Yue!

380
00:38:44,240 --> 00:38:45,840
Why are you hanging around me?

381
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:51,400
I want to know why you picked "Comrade
Saeng"? It's so outdated, and lame.

382
00:38:53,240 --> 00:38:59,920
It suits you. Doesn't your
real name mean "the sun"?

383
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:09,520
Urgh!!!

384
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:12,079
Thank you so much for saving me.

385
00:39:12,080 --> 00:39:15,280
My name is Ravin. You can call me Vin.

386
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:18,119
Oh, from when I took a dump.

387
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:22,120
Hey Comrade! Hurry up and take it.

388
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:39,040
Yay!

389
00:39:39,080 --> 00:39:40,040
I'd go with that one over there.

390
00:39:40,041 --> 00:39:42,040
Ugh... Argh!

391
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:44,480
Hey! Fine, It's yours.
I'll take the other one.

392
00:39:48,680 --> 00:39:51,200
Let's see what we've got here..

393
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:55,080
Whoa, there's a flashlight!

394
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:57,760
Mmmm... A flashlight.

395
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:08,400
Are you OK, Comrade Saeng?

396
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:15,400
Hey Comrade Saeng! Don't you hear me?

397
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:21,280
Comrade Gaun Hin is speaking
to you, Comrade Saeng.

398
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:24,440
Shit! Did you call me?

399
00:40:26,440 --> 00:40:30,920
No more "shit". You were just named
"Comrade Saeng." Did you forget?

400
00:40:32,640 --> 00:40:35,800
Sorry. I forgot.

401
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:39,399
What are you trying to say?

402
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:43,039
I asked you, "Are you OK with it?"

403
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:47,360
Oh, that's it? No need to make
it sound so formal. That's easy.

404
00:40:52,280 --> 00:40:55,280
Are you done with your belongings?
So go take a shower.

405
00:40:55,304 --> 00:40:56,224
Finished.

406
00:40:56,401 --> 00:40:57,600
Go take a shower.

407
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:02,680
Go take a shower. We're so stinky.

408
00:41:20,040 --> 00:41:20,960
Get down.

409
00:41:20,961 --> 00:41:23,919
Woohoo!

410
00:41:23,920 --> 00:41:26,479
Finally, it's shower time! I'm so stinky.

411
00:41:26,480 --> 00:41:27,559
Yay!

412
00:41:27,560 --> 00:41:28,480
Woohoo!

413
00:41:28,480 --> 00:41:29,480
Woohoo!

414
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:32,320
This is not a playground.

415
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:38,240
If your noise drowns out the warning siren,
you won't escape in time.

416
00:41:38,920 --> 00:41:40,040
Especially you.

417
00:41:41,560 --> 00:41:44,360
What the hell? Why me?
